node.text: @radenmas662 NKF saga is a good example not all charitable organizations can be trusted. There are other examples too.

Malaysia-based Singaporean actor Aaron Aziz has spent RM50,000 (S$16,500) to distribute essential supplies to the less fortunate during Malaysia’s MCO (Movement Control Order). Through his organisation Journey to Insyirah, Aziz relayed help to close to 1,000 needy individuals and families across Malaysia, including Pahang, Melaka, Johor, Perlis, Kedah, Selangor and Kuala Lumpur. “I hope that whatever we do will be of help to the needy at this moment," he said. 🇸🇬🇲🇾💪#AaronAziz #charity #philanthropy #Singapore #Malaysia #MCO #coronavairus #COVID19 #CNAlifestyle (Pic: 8days.sg)
